CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 8, reads: "The Willard Jeffersons - Miss Helen L. Brown and Willard M. Jefferson were married June 28th by the Rev. T. J. King. A pretty reception was held at the Northside Elks' Hall.  The couple left for an Eastern honeymoon.  The bride is the daughter of the Arthur Browns; the groom, the son of the Clarence Jeffersons. - (Harris photo).
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five women, including bride Helen L. Brown Jefferson wearing gown with sheer feather pattern, and three men, including groom Willard M. Jefferson, cutting three tiered wedding cake, in Northside Elks Lodge
